* mtime, atime, and ctime
- ctime: or 'change time'. is the time when changes were made to the file or directory's inode (owner, permissions, etc.). __The ctime is also updated when the contents of a file change.__
ctime can be showed by 'ls -lc'

- atime:is the time when the data of a file was last accessed. can be showed by 'ls -lu'

- mtime: is the time when the actual contents of a file was last modified. This is the time displayed in a long directoring listing 'ls -l'.

